### 3. Create your first Revealjs Presentation Slides

1.  <div>

    1.  Now, use your MSDM CEP Project. 

    2.  Create a reveal presentation slides as a separate project in your local drive.

    3.  Add at least one reproducible chart or table In the presentation. For example, you can read your data in a code chunk and use in-line coding to provide sample-size information in your narrative as in the example provided in the previous page.

    4.  Make sure that your storytelling is clear in the slides. For example, you can write a story around your analytics objectives as follows.

        1.  Title page

        2.  Table of Contents

        3.  Introduction

            1.  Problem statement

            2.  One Analytics Objective

            3.  Importance

        4.  Literature review

            1.  Existence of well-established consumer behavior theory/models relevant for the project

            2.  Assessment of the adequateness of the gathered information/data in solving business problems

            3.  Need for additional analysis to address the said business problems?

        5.  Methods

            1.  Data and Sampling

            2.  Data wrangling

            3.  Sample characteristics

            4.  Measures

            5.  Analytics Methods

        6.  References

    5.  Publish it on the web (e.g., Quarto-pub) as you learned previously.

    </div>
